headline: Wells Fargo Confirms Termination of 2021 OCC Loss Mitigation Consent Order
summary: SAN FRANCISCO, March 17, 2025--Wells Fargo & Company (NYSE: WFC) today confirmed that the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency (OCC) terminated its 2021 consent order related to loss mitigation practices in the company’s Home Lending business. This is the eleventh consent order closed by Wells Fargo’s regulators since 2019.
